snippet.textDisplay:
the style of patiala gharana and sabri gharana being showcased here, Rahat singing his parts the way NFAK has sung and Amjad Sabri singing his parts, the way his father and uncle sang. Both the artists showcasing the legacy of their gharana's, just wow.
Moreover the track has been sung and recorded directly, skipping the rehearsal. Who needs a rehearsal when the maestros of the genre of this time are going to perform. Both the artists interacting with each other using hand gestures while singing and letting each other sing their best. Plus the smiling gestures exchange with the director on set, tells us that this is the first and final go and is not rehearsed. Awesome.
A single composition and two different gharana styles coming together and nailed it.
I wonder what a master piece would that have been which Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan and Ustad Ghulam Fareed Sabri had sung on a darga together in a single go. Couldn't find a video where these two are singing together.
Well thank you Coke Studio, Strings, Shani Arshad and most importantly Amjad Sabri (late) and Rahat Fateh Ali Khan for giving us a treat with a taste of both the legendary gharanas in one single track.
The kalaam has many lyrics, the qawali could go longer. These 12 minutes seems very less for such a big one from CS.
